Sentencas: As a cathode material for proton-conducting SOFCs (H-SOFCs), a novel MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 (MCSO) spinel material was suggested.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The MCSO material was effectively produced, and it demonstrated excellent phase stability at elevated temperatures and chemical stability against CO2 and H2O.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Doping Sb into the MnCo2O4 (MCO) allowed for enhanced proton diffusion and surface exchange, as evidenced by electrical conductivity relaxation tests.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, an oxygen-vacancy-rich surface was developed for the MCSO material, resulting in the possibility of a high cathode oxygen reduction reaction activity.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The MCSO material was examined in the H-SOFC application, and the fuel cell with an MCSO cathode attained a high power density of 1380 mW cm-2 at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the cell employing the Sb-free MCO cathode, which had a comparable cell microstructure to the MCSO cell, only obtained a peak power density of 836 mW cm-2.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The higher cell performance resulted from the Sbmodified MCO cathode's increased catalytic activity.
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the MCSO cell displayed excellent operational stability under fuel cell operating conditions, indicating that MCSO is a novel and effective spinel cathode for H-SOFCs.(c) 2023
Titulo: A new and robust MnCo1.9Sb0.1O4 spinel cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
